OL,3,CJersey Gambling Commission report
OL,4,Ccalls for on-island treatment centre
OL,6,FLast year, there were plans to work
OL,7,Fwith an overseas specialist to treat
OL,8,Fproblem gamblers in Jersey, but the
OL,9,Fproject fell through.
OL,11,FThe Commission also recently
OL,12,Fdiscontinued its Gambling Therapy
OL,13,Fservice due to low uptake, with the
OL,14,Freport highlighting that establishing
OL,15,Fa local service is "all the more
OL,16,Fimportant."
